  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "Memory corruption due to improper authentication in Qualcomm IPC while loading unsigned lib in audio PD.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2022-33242 describes a software/firmware vulnerability in Qualcomm IPC that allows memory corruption when loading unsigned libraries in the audio processing domain. The affected component is a driver/IPC used on Snapdragon SoCs, which is part of the software stack that runs general-purpose AI workloads on such hardware. This constitutes a software supply-chain entry affecting AI deployment stacks, with a known vulnerability (CVE) and explicit references."
  },
